                <h1>Painting Over Wallpaper in Your Bathroom: Tips & Tricks</h1>
                <p>Yes, you can paint over wallpaper in a bathroom, but preparation is key. Clean the wallpaper to remove any grime, and make sure it's securely adhered to the wall. Use a primer suitable for the wallpaper type to ensure paint adhesion. Choose a mold-resistant paint to withstand moisture. This method can rejuvenate your bathroom's look without the hassle of removing the wallpaper.</p>
